{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "lxxe:proverbs.1",
    "translationId": "lxxe",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 1,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 1 in Brenton's English Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.1.1",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:1",
      "text": "The Proverbs of Solomon son of David, who reigned in Israel;",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.1.2",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:2",
      "text": "to know wisdom and instruction, and to perceive words of understanding;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.1.3",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:3",
      "text": "to receive also hard saying, and to understand true justice, and how to direct judgement;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.1.4",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:4",
      "text": "that he might give subtlety to the simple, and to the young man discernment and understanding.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.1.5",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:5",
      "text": "For by the hearing of these a wise man will be wiser, and man of understanding will gain direction;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.1.6",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:6",
      "text": "and will understand a parable, and a dark speech; the saying of the wise also, and riddles.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.1.7",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:7",
      "text": "The fear of the Lord is the beginning of wisdom; and there is good understanding to all that practise it: and piety toward God is the beginning of discernment; but the ungodly will set at nought wisdom and instruction.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.1.8",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:8",
      "text": "Hear, my son, the instruction of thy father, and reject not the rules of thy mother.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.1.9",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:9",
      "text": "For thou shalt receive for thine head a crown of graces, and a chain of gold round thy neck.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.1.10",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:10",
      "text": "My son, let not ungodly men lead thee astray, neither consent thou to them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.1.11",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:11",
      "text": "If they should exhort thee, saying, Come with us, partake in blood, and let us unjustly hide the just man in the earth:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.1.12",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:12",
      "text": "and let us swallow him alive, as Hades would, and remove the memorial of him from the earth:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.1.13",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:13",
      "text": "let us seize on his valuable property, and let us fill our houses with spoils:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.1.14",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:14",
      "text": "but do thou cast in thy lot with us, and let us all provide a common purse, and let us have one pouch:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.1.15",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:15",
      "text": "go not in the way with them, but turn aside thy foot from their paths:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.1.17",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:17",
      "text": "for nets are not without cause spread for birds.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.1.18",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:18",
      "text": "For they that are concerned in murder store up evils for themselves; and the overthrow of transgressors is evil.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.1.19",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:19",
      "text": "These are the ways of all that perform lawless deeds; for by ungodliness they destroy their own life.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.1.20",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:20",
      "text": "Wisdom sings aloud in passages, and in the broad places speaks boldly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.1.21",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:21",
      "text": "And she makes proclamation on the top of the walls, and sits by the gates of princes; and at the gates of the city boldly says,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.1.22",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:22",
      "text": "So long as the simple cleave to justice, they shall not be ashamed: but the foolish being lovers of haughtiness, having become ungodly have hated knowledge, and are become subject to reproofs.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.1.23",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:23",
      "text": "Behold, I will bring forth to you the utterance of my breath, and I will instruct you in my speech.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.1.24",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:24",
      "text": "Since I called, and ye did not hearken; and I spoke at length, and ye gave no heed;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.1.25",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:25",
      "text": "but ye set at nought my counsels, and disregarded my reproofs;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.1.26",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:26",
      "text": "therefore I also will laugh at your destruction; and I will rejoice against you when ruin comes upon you:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.1.27",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:27",
      "text": "yea when dismay suddenly comes upon you, and your overthrow shall arrive like a tempest; and when tribulation and distress shall come upon you, or when ruin shall come upon you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.1.28",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:28",
      "text": "For it shall be that when ye call upon me, I will not hearken to you: wicked men shall seek me, but shall not find me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.1.29",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:29",
      "text": "For they hated wisdom, and did not choose the word of the Lord:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.1.30",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:30",
      "text": "neither would they attend to my counsels, but derided my reproofs.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.1.31",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:31",
      "text": "Therefore shall they eat the fruits of their own way, and shall be filled with their own ungodliness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.1.32",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:32",
      "text": "For because they wronged the simple, they shall be slain; and an inquisition shall ruin the ungodly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.1.33",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:33",
      "text": "But he that hearkens to me shall dwell in confidence, and shall rest securely from all evil.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
